It's the best looking gun I own, and my wife loves it. This is a picture I took at the range, where I was shooting a small plate at 200 yards. Quite a few people have been curious to see me shooting at 200 yards with a 22. It is pushing pretty far for the little 22lr, but this rifle and scope can do it easily, with any ammo. Of course, you'll get better results with feeding it nicer stuff. CCI standard velocity works well with this rifle and is very clean, but tends to run out of energy at longer ranges. It's also one of the cheapest types of 22 ammo, but is has very waxy lubricant, and tends to jam up semi-autos. That's one of the benefits of a bolt action 22 - you can work with more types of ammo. Just keep the chamber clean - this is a target gun and has tight tolerances. I just brush the chamber out a bit if too much lubricant has accumulated.

title: For Sale:  Sig 9mm P239 CCP German Made
postcontent: For sale or trade, I offer this Sig Sauer P 239 CCP (Conceal Carry Pistol) 9mm. Frame marked: made in Germany. This harder to find "blue box" German 9mm in excellent condition has EVERYTHING, Sig Lites, Nitron finish, DA/SA, de-horned with cockable bobbed hammer, 3 mags, 2 sets of grips (factory composites) and Sig badged hogue's, Sig branded Israeli made fobus OWB holster and matching double magazine carrier. The Sig P 239, although a little smaller (for concealment reasons) than its big brother, the P 229, also has a proven track record with numerous U.S. as well as international governmental agencies ranging from the FBI, Immigration & Customs Enforcement (ICE),  Dept. Homeland Security and countless other undercover agencies ranging from NCIS to Israel's clandestine elite Mossad and numerous others, especially when configured in the CCP variant. Furthermore, Sig's P 239 routinely ranks high on most lists and reviews of the best conceal carry pistols.I have had this gun in addition to another P 239 and also its big brother the P 229. My observations: the 239 is an absolute joy to shoot and has excellent weight distribution, giving the operator exceptional accuracy, a large trigger guard opening large enough to fire it with most gloves should the need arise and as seen in the photos, this oversized trigger guard which angles to the front of its aluminum frame contributes to nice weight distribution as well as making it rather comfortable in the waistband even against skin. The P 239 is slimmer and has much cleaner lines than the larger P 229. As the gun was intended for concealed carry from its prototypes day one. A very different concept from other high-end contenders, which are essentially a full-size pistol chopped down at the barrel and the bottom of the handle, which works but unfortunately sacrifices performance most all of the time. This is NOT a concern with Sigs P 239 CCP. I have numerous high-quality handguns, many in 9mm, I assure you whether you're at the range or, God forbid, a real-life scenario, the P 239 will not disappoint. Of all my pistols of this kind, only one out-performs this Sig, that gun is an HK P7 M8. The P7 M8 is a totally different animal, however. Although they are similar size-wise the HK P7 M8 costing about twice the price, the P7 M8 is a fixed-barrel steel frame "gas gun." Its groupings are a little tighter than the Sig but by no means are they substantially tighter and most shooters probably wouldn't see much difference on the target. And even for a great shot, the HK's tighter grouping doesn't compensate for the many advantages the Sig P 239 has over the HK. The Sig is a good bit lighter due to its alloy frame, neither have ever given me any "FTFs" (Failure to feed) and/or "FTEs" (Failure to eject). Nor are either ammo picky. The Sig is not only a good bit cleaner but also easier to clean, unlike the HK a gas gun, which are notorious for carbon build-up, (not range-friendly). In my opinion, the Sig is a much more carry-friendly pistol, because it's a lighter gun and has far more options holster-wise. If you really want to shoot an HK P7 M8, ideally you need a pair as this gun gets hotter than any pistol I've ever shot, this is also a non-issue with the Sig. Lastly, parts for a Sig P 239 can be easily located. That said, if I did not have two P 239s I would NOT sell or trade this gun especially because not only is this a fine German Sig, but this is also a full set with everything including its blank lifetime warranty paperwork. German Sigs, in general, are becoming harder and harder to come by, forget about a 9mm P 239 in pristine condition and a complete set. This Sig was my desk drawer gun and the pictures attest that it's been carried only a handful of times. Round count 5 boxes of 50 brass FMJ and 3 magazines of various PP loads while deciding which I'd use. *Note the other P 239 also 9mm has been shot 3 to 4 times more, and is now my wife's primary carry gun. The CCP variant really doesn't matter to her as the gun is kept in her purse. As for trades, I'm a bit picky as I know what I like and what I have so trades preferred: a bull-barrel high-end single-stack 1911 .45 ACP, Benelli M1 or M2, Colt revolvers and perhaps a Belgian Browning Hi-Power 9mm. I may be open to other hard to find high-quality pistols. Although not a pawn shop, I will also consider fine Swiss-made mechanical watches, diamond solitaires, solid gold and platinum jewelry, Morgan and Liberty silver dollars and various gold coins. Being a collector, I am interested in a variety of neat and cool items so feel free to message me but I'm really looking for the items above or cash. (As much of what I'm looking for is more valuable than this Sig, cash or additional trade on my end of course.)Face-to-face transactions preferred with proper ID either your CWP or driver's license, Missouri only. You must also be of legal age and lawfully able to purchase a firearm. I am not an FFL dealer, law enforcement or military. Still, verification of MO residency and a bill of sale will be completed. If you do not know whether you have a warrant for your arrest, or are unable to lawfully possess a firearm, I would advise you contact the MO Highway Patrol or your local sheriff's department for this information. Lastly, if this ad is "POSTED" then the gun is still available. Please do not send emails asking whether the gun is still available. I will remove the listing once it's sold. I am by no means desperate to sell nor need assistance in selling. All reasonable offers will be considered.  -Thank you
